<HEADLINE> Predators' President Has Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Jack Diller, president of the NHL's  
Nashville Predators, has had quadruple-bypass surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Diller, 60, had the surgery Monday at St. Thomas Hospital and is  
now in a critical care unit. 
</P>
<P>
	A test last week showed that the four arteries needed to be  
cleared. 
</P>
<P>
	Before taking the Predators' job, Diller was president and chief  
executive officer of the NBA's San Antonio Spurs. He also has been 
president of the Madison Square Garden Sports Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
