<P>
	House Panel Concludes Chinese Spying  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton said today, with a  
bipartisan House report that Chinese spying has obtained top-secret 
information about every U.S. nuclear weapon he will enact more than 
two dozen recommendations to safeguard America's nuclear secrets. 
During an appearance in Texas, Clinton said his administration was 
moving aggressively to tighten security at nuclear laboratories and 
would work with Congress to follow the recommendations of the 
special committee. But he also said the administration would keep 
on dealing with China on a range of matters because that, too, was 
in the national interest. 

</P>
<P>
	Gore Courts Female Voters for 2000  
</P>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Al Gore is making a special appeal to  
female voters, building a list of thousands of women for a mass 
endorsement the vice president plans to announce next week. The 
pitch came in the form of a letter sent to women across the 
country. In outlining what they say are Gore's accomplishments on 
women's issues, two congresswomen cite his support for abortion 
rights, equal pay for women, child care credits for the poor and 
the Family and Medical Leave Act. 

