<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Guilty in Photographer Beating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- A man was convicted of attempted  
murder Monday in an attack on a newspaper photographer who was 
beaten by as many as 12 people after he stopped by a playground to 
take pictures of children. 
</P>
<P>
	Terauchi Kenkiuchi Golston, a 26-year-old reputed gang member,  
could get 21 years to life in prison at sentencing June 23 in the 
1997 attack on Sacramento Bee photographer John Trotter. 
</P>
<P>
	Four juveniles are already serving sentences for their roles.  
</P>
<P>
	Trotter was beaten unconscious. He suffered memory trouble,  
numbness and psychological trauma and has been unable to return to 
work. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors said Golston saw Trotter as an intruder in the  
neighborhood and assaulted him after Trotter refused to hand over 
his film. 
</P>
<P>
	Golston's lawyers said a mother had initially confronted  
Trotter, fearing he was a pedophile. Trotter was carrying two 
cameras and wearing a Sacramento Bee cap at the time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
