	The British pound was quoted at $1.6018, up from $1.5961.  
</P>
<P>
	Midday in New York, the dollar bought 122.78 yen, while the euro  
was worth $1.0574 and the pound traded at $1.5955. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8469 German marks, down from 1.8497; 
