<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Versace Family Halts Book </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The family of Gianni Versace has effectively  
stopped the publication of an unauthorized biography of the slain 
fashion designer, The New York Times reported today. 
</P>
<P>
	``Undressed: The Life and Times of Gianni Versace,'' by  
Christopher Mason, was in galley form and set for publication July 
1 before its cancellation by Little, Brown, a division of Time 
Warner. 
</P>
<P>
	The Times reported that the book would have depicted Versace as  
a colossal talent who was promiscuous, bullied employees and 
berated journalists who wrote unkind reviews of his collections. 
</P>
<P>
	The book also would have been unflattering to Versace's  
surviving siblings, Santo and Donatella, who assumed control of his 
$560 million fashion empire after his 1997 murder, The Times said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mason says representatives for the Versaces, in their bid to  
stop the book, contacted people he had interviewed and tried to 
persuade them to recant their statements. 
</P>
<P>
	Little, Brown said it had received letters threatening legal  
action from the Versaces, had agreed with Mason that the book 
couldn't be published in its current form and was concerned that 
the biography, which was postponed last July, would be unable to 
sustain interest after another delay. 
</P>
<P>
	The Versaces, through their press agents, said they were  
satisfied with the decision to kill the book and denied there were 
any attempts to intimidate sources. 
</P>
<P>
	The family said their objections to the biography were based on  
Mason's shoddy reporting, not on unflattering depictions of the 
Versaces. 
</P>
<P>
	The ``Undressed'' manuscript underwent legal reviews last winter  
and this spring. It largely passed the scrutiny of the publisher's 
lawyers, Mason said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I felt completely confident about my reporting, and I had  
substantial documentation,'' Mason said. ``The book isn't coming 
out. They won.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
