<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-25 05:42:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gingrich Discusses Cultural 'Decay' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Republicans shouldn't be gloomy about their  
prospects in the 2000 congressional elections just because the GOP 
lost seats in the House last time, former House Speaker Newt 
Gingrich says. 
</P>
<P>
	Gingrich said in a speech Monday night that Republicans can run  
on their successes since taking over Congress in 1994, such as 
welfare reform, tax cuts, a balanced federal budget and proposals 
to set up private savings accounts as an alternative to Social 
Security for younger people. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm an optimist. We are a majority,'' he said. ``We have, in  
fact, had an impact.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gingrich, who resigned from Congress after the GOP losses in the  
1998 elections, also touched on school violence and foreign policy 
in his speech to $10,000-level donors to GOPAC, a political action 
committee he once led. 
</P>
<P>
	On school violence, the Georgia Republican said incidents like  
the Colorado and Georgia school shootings will never be solved 
without changes such as voluntary school prayer, competency tests 
for teachers and lower taxes intended to reduce the need for two 
parents to work. 
</P>
<P>
	``I believe there is, in fact, a decay in the land,'' Gingrich  
said. ``The liberals yell, 'Gun control,' because it's the only 
thing they've got.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gingrich also said students should be taught the Declaration of  
Independence closely, particularly its section about rights to 
``life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness'' guaranteed by a 
``creator,'' so that they will look at each human life as valuable. 
</P>
<P>
	``If you've had it drilled into you that you are a child of God  
... you're creating a much greater sense of civility,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Gingrich had harsh criticism for President Clinton's handling of  
the conflict in Yugoslavia, calling it the ``worst-managed American 
campaign since the Spanish-American War. It is a tragedy on every 
front.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The war has exposed flaws in the U.S. intelligence system that  
shows the need for greater resources, he added. And he put in a 
pitch for a U.S. missile defense system, particularly if the 
Chinese and others gain ground in their nuclear capabilities. 
</P>
<P>
	GOPAC officials said the speech is likely to become one of the  
thousands of audio tapes the group sends to Republican candidates 
nationwide to help them articulate the party agenda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
