<HEADLINE> Harrist Named Jackson News Editor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Ron Harrist, who has worked for The  
Associated Press in Jackson for more than three decades, has been 
promoted to news editor. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Tuesday by Mississippi Chief of  
Bureau Frank Fisher. 
</P>
<P>
	Harrist joined the AP in 1968 in Jackson. He became state editor  
in the mid-1970s, while Jackson was still a correspondency, and he 
continued in that capacity when the state was elevated to bureau 
status in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Harrist, 56, was born in Tampa, Fla., and grew up in east Texas.  
He is a graduate of Mississippi College in Clinton and worked for 
The (Jackson) Clarion-Ledger before joining the AP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
