<HEADLINE> AP Names Batog Milwaukee News Ed. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Jennifer A. Batog, a newswoman in the Milwaukee  
bureau of The Associated Press, has been promoted to news editor 
for Wisconsin. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Tuesday by Chief of Bureau T. Lee  
Hughes. 
</P>
<P>
	Batog, 25, joined the AP in 1996 as an editorial assistant in  
Washington. She was promoted to newswoman the following year in 
Milwaukee, where she has worked as a reporter and desk editor. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining the AP, Batog graduated from George Washington  
University and worked for The Middlesex News in Framingham, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
	She succeeds David Germain, who is transferring to Los Angeles  
as a business writer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
