<HEADLINE> Greg Louganis To Appear in Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Greg Louganis is set to plunge into a new role  
this week when he appears in a production of the play ``Just Say 
No.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The four-time diving Olympic gold medalist will play Junior in  
Larry Kramer's 1988 farce. 
</P>
<P>
	The production opens Thursday at Chicago's Bailiwick Repertory  
as part of the PRIDE '99 series of plays and performances. 
</P>
<P>
	Louganis, who revealed his homosexuality in 1994 and a year  
later acknowledged that he has AIDS, portrays a gay character who 
decides to move to the city to become a ballet dancer. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm happy with where I am,'' Louganis said Monday. ``I'm  
happier with who I am.'' 
</P>
