<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> French Open Tennis Notebook </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- The Williams sisters have picked their favorites to  
win the French Open: themselves. 
</P>
<P>
	``Don't be surprised if one of the Williams sisters decides it  
is red clay time,'' Serena writes in the sisters' newsletter, ``The 
Tennis Monthly Recap.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The newsletter lists ``Serena J.'' as chief editor and ``Venus  
Ebony Star'' as chief writer. 
</P>
<P>
	Big sister Venus considers her chances of winning in an article  
called, ``The world according to Venus.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Obviously, Venus will go into the French as a favorite and if  
the world turns according to the way Venus has planned, you can 
already guess who will be holding the 1999 French Open trophy,'' 
she writes. 
</P>
<P>
	Serena likes her own chances.  
</P>
<P>
	``At last year's French, Serena succumbed to the villain of  
inexperience, but don't expect Serena to fall into the same trap 
this year,'' she writes in an article called, ``Serena, Serena, 
Serena!'' 
</P>
<P>
	As for the men's tournament, the sisters are rooting for their  
favorite player, Pete Sampras. 
</P>
<P>
	``Pete can do it. But a small word of advice Pete: Play your  
game. We believe in you!'' Serena writes. 
</P>
<P>
	Sampras barely escaped elimination in the first round on  
Tuesday, beating 92nd-ranked Juan Antonio Marin of Costa Rica, 6-7 
(5-7), 6-4, 7-5, 6-7 (9-11), 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *GIDDYUP:* Tennis players who make a good impression on the  
Roland Garros crowds could go home on horseback. 
</P>
<P>
	PMU, the major French racing bookmaker, is giving away a race  
horse to the player tournament spectators vote as their favorite. 
The race horse is worth $49,000 but winners cannot just take the 
money. Not every player can house a racehorse in their backyard, so 
PMU will take care of everything for a year. 
</P>
<P>
	``We could come across someone who isn't used to caring for a  
horse,'' said PMU spokesman Jean-Jacques Peyrouzelle. ``The horse 
will be fed, housed and trained for one year to ensure the proper 
care in the beginning.'' 
</P>
<P>
	After the year is up, the player can sell the horse or keep  
paying for its upkeep and enter it in races. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *SOCCER FAN STEFFI:* Steffi Graf will take a break from the  
French Open on Wednesday to cheer on Bayern Munich in soccer's 
European Champions League final. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very interested in soccer and Bayern Munich is one of my  
two favorite teams,'' said Graf, who is bidding for her sixth 
French Open championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Graf admits to not giving the German team her undivided loyalty.  
</P>
<P>
	``Because my boyfriend always watches Schalke 04, I have become  
a follower of that team too,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bayern plays England's Manchester United in Barcelona in the  
showpiece match of the European soccer season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
