</P>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Steve Finley hurt his old team again last night,  
driving in three runs with a single and double as the Arizona 
Diamondbacks beat the San Diego Padres 6-5. Finley, who had two 
home runs in his first game for Arizona in San Diego on April 23, 
singled with the bases loaded in the first inning to drive in two 
runs, then added an RBI double in the third. Andy Benes, a loser in 
his last three starts, got the victory. 

</P>
