</P>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Kevin Millar hit a bizarre three-run,  
inside-the-park homer with two outs in the ninth inning off new 
Chicago reliever Rick Aguilera and the Florida Marlins rallied with 
four runs to stun the Cubs 7-5 last night. Chicago had a 5-3 lead 
headed into the ninth but Aguilera surrendered singles to Bruce 
Aven, Luis Castillo and Cliff Floyd to make it 5-4. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by VINCENT K. WILLIS  
</P>
