<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> S.Korea Wants 2010 Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- Muju, a resort village in South Korea,  
will officially open a campaign to serve as the host for the 2010 
Winter Olympics by launching a bid committee Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The committee will be led by Kim Un-yong, chairman of the Korean  
Olympic Committee and an executive board member of the 
International Olympic Committee. 
</P>
<P>
	Muju's bid has been endorsed by the Korean Olympic Committee.  
Muju, 120 miles southeast of Seoul, was the site of the 1997 Winter 
University Games. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of 18 facilities are needed for a site to serve as a  
host for the Winter Olympics. Muju plans to use 11 existing 
facilities and build the others, officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The site for the 2010 Winter Olympics will be selected by 2003.  
</P>
<P>
	The Winter Games have been staged only twice in Asia -- in Japan  
in 1972 and 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Seoul, South Korea's capital, was host to the 1988 Summer Games.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
